### Issue 9: Race Condition on File Read

Use retry logic or file sharing mode:

```csharp
// Replace line 331:
var json = File.ReadAllText(file);

// With:
string json;
try
{
    using var stream = new FileStream(file, FileMode.Open, FileAccess.Read, FileShare.ReadWrite);
    using var reader = new StreamReader(stream);
    json = reader.ReadToEnd();
}
catch (IOException)
{
    continue; // Skip file if currently being written
}
```

---

### Issue 10: Silent Exception Swallowing

Add logging for history persistence failures:

```csharp
// Replace lines 223-227:
catch
{
    // Best-effort history persistence — don't fail the execution
}

// With:
catch (Exception historyEx)
{
    logger.LogWarning(historyEx, "Failed to persist execution history for {ExecutionId}", executionId);
}
```

---

### Issue 11: Unbounded Channel

Add a bounded channel with a reasonable capacity:

```csharp
// In WebOrchestrationReporter.cs, change the channel creation (line 19):
// From:
private readonly Channel<SseEvent> _channel = Channel.CreateUnbounded<SseEvent>();

// To:
private readonly Channel<SseEvent> _channel = Channel.CreateBounded<SseEvent>(
    new BoundedChannelOptions(1000)
    {
        FullMode = BoundedChannelFullMode.Wait
    });
```

---

### Issue 12: ConcurrentDictionary Cleanup

The cleanup at line 262 handles normal cases. For edge cases, add periodic cleanup:

```csharp
// This is lower priority - the using statement on line 160 already handles most cases.
// For orphaned entries from crashes, consider adding a background timer:

// Option: Add timeout-based cleanup (add after app.Run() setup)
var cleanupTimer = new Timer(_ =>
{
    foreach (var kvp in activeExecutions)
    {
        if (kvp.Value.IsCancellationRequested)
        {
            if (activeExecutions.TryRemove(kvp.Key, out var cts))
                cts.Dispose();
        }
    }
}, null, TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5), TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5));
```
